# Production Environment Variables for Vercel

## Required Variables

### Database
```
DATABASE_URL=<from-vercel-postgres-dashboard>
```
Get this from: Vercel Dashboard → Your Project → Storage → Postgres → .env.local tab

### NextAuth
```
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=<generate-secure-random-string>
NEXTAUTH_URL=https://your-domain.vercel.app
```

Generate NEXTAUTH_SECRET with:
```bash
openssl rand -base64 32
```

### Cloudinary (if using image uploads)
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your-cloud-name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your-api-key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your-api-secret
```

## How to Set in Vercel

1. Go to Vercel Dashboard
2. Select your project
3. Go to Settings → Environment Variables
4. Add each variable above
5. Select all environments (Production, Preview, Development)
6. Click "Save"

## Important Notes

- **DATABASE_URL**: Automatically provided by Vercel Postgres
- **NEXTAUTH_URL**: Must match your production domain (e.g., `https://yoursite.vercel.app`)
- **NEXTAUTH_SECRET**: Must be a secure random string (at least 32 characters)
- Never commit actual values to Git - use this as a reference only
